text: Even if this is my own list, maintaining it has introduced me to a lot of games I wouldn't have normally known about. I discovered a lot of the more obscure games while searching for hidden audio gems. You know how you can visit a Wikipedia page, then click on a related link, then another one, etc. and just end up on a completely different page than the first one you searched for? That tends to happen a lot when I search for game music. I discovered this while searching for Pop'n Music tracks a couple months ago.
